        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16568",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I expect the following:\n\nThe default Time within your locale is something like that:\n\"HH:mm:ss a\"\n\nwhich means that your standard time is only allowed from 0-11 and you have an meridiem which seperates morning and afternoon. So you have 01:00:00 pm and 01:00:00 am...\nThis means that a time like \"22:00:00\" is not possible in your locale, you would have to set a proper meridiem.\n\nPlease provide the following data:\n\nYour set locale in the script\nYour set timezone in the script\nIf you use BCMath\n\nThe used version of ZF... before committing an bug please check always against the latest SVN version.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-09T03:54:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-09T03:54:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16571",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If I add the locale to the object, then it works well.\n\n{code}\ndate_default_timezone_set('Asia\/Taipei');\n$lo = new Zend_Locale(\"zh_tw\");\n$a = Zend_Date::now($lo);\n\necho $a->getIso($lo).\"\\n\";\n\n$a->setTime(\"22:13:14\");\n\necho $a->getIso($lo).\"\\n\";\n{code}\n\nBut would it be possible determine the time assigned automatically, rather than the time was decreased 12 hours.\n\nZF 1.0.1, Rev.5906\nBCMath enabled.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-09T06:45:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-09T06:45:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16572",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "How Zend_Date works on localized data depends on the given locale...\nIf you do not provide a locale to Zend_Date it tries to automatically detect the locale from your browser or environment.\n\nIn the docu it's declared that always a locale should be set... as sometimes the locale can not be detected because the server does not provide one. In such environments localized inputs for I18N classes do not work.\n\nAs your script works when you give \"zh_tw\" per hand it means also that your default script is another one.\n\nPlease provide your \"default\" locale for futher inventigation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-09T07:25:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-09T07:25:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16574",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{code}\nZend_Date::setOptions(array(\"format_type\" => \"php\"));\n$lo = new Zend_Locale ( \"Asia\/Taipei\" ) ;\n$currentTime = new Zend_Date(\"2007-9-1\", null, $lo) ;\n$currentTime->setTime(\"14:12:10\", \"H:i:s\",$lo);\n$endTime = clone $currentTime ;\n$endTime = $endTime->addMonth ( 3 ) ;\n\necho \"Current time:\" . $currentTime->getIso ($lo) . \"\\n\" ;\necho \"End time:\" . $endTime->getIso ($lo) . \"\\n\" ;\n{code}\nExports:\nCurrent time:2007-09-01T14:12:10+00:00\nEnd time:2007-12-01T14:12:10+00:00\n\nIf add date_default_timezone_set\n{code}\ndate_default_timezone_set ( 'Asia\/Taipei' ) ;\n{code}\n\nThen it exports:\nCurrent time:2007-09-01T14:12:10+08:00\nEnd time:2007-12-01T14:12:10+08:00\n\nIs this correct ? I assigned the Zend_Locale, but it still stay the GMT timezone.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-09T10:34:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-09T10:34:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16575",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please provide your default locale for further investigation\nSee PHP's setlocale() an how to do this.\n\nRelated to your second issue...\n\nIf you have 01.Sept.2007 14:12:10 and add 3 months you will receive the 01.Dec.2007 14:12:10... I see no failure on this.\n\nAnd your output from ISO says \"+08:00\" which means that it is no longer in GMT but in GMT + 8 hours... also here I see no failure.\n\nFor questions on how Zend_Date works feel free to ask within our mailinglists fw-i18n@zend.com or fw-general@zend.com.\n\nPS: Timezones and Locales are two things... they have nothing to do with each other. Locales are used to localize and normalize input and to receive locale informations. Timezones just define the offset to calculate for a date \/ time. A user with the locale \"en_US\" could also have a timezone of \"GMT+2\" if he wishes.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-09T12:17:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-09T12:17:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16781",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As we are not getting feedback we are closing this ticket.\nFrom the respone it seems that there is only a misunderstanding and not a failure.\n\nFeel free to reopen this ticket if you think its not fixed and you are able to provide the needed data for reproduction for us.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
